b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":406,"category_name":"News","pr_category_id":"1","title_name":"High Mercury\'s Trial Added to Advanced Dragon Trials!","message":"<div>High Mercury&#39;s Trial was added to the Advanced Dragon Trials, the most challenging of event quests, at <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1555567200\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>With both strength and kindness, Mercury uses her immense mana to coat her body. Prepare yourself for battle!<\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/a9d746598e736ef0e8ce62100de92371.png\\"><\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Changes accompanying the release of High Mercury&#39;s Trial:<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>1. High Mercury and the Fafnir Statue (Water) facility were added to the Advanced Dragon Trials section of Treasure Trade.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The High Mercury dragon is described below.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Stats<\/div><div>\\u30fbLv 100\/100<\/div><div>\\u30fbHP 357<\/div><div>\\u30fbStrength 113<\/div><div>\\u30fbMight 1070<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Dragon Details<\/div><div>The Waterwyrm Mercury after releasing her true powers. Her immense mana acts as a great current that coats her body. With the kindness to protect those she cares for&mdash;and the strength to repel all threats&mdash;she&#39;s a truly wondrous dragon.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Skills<\/div><div>\\u30fbAqua Spiral<\/div><div>Deals water damage to surrounding enemies, draws them toward the user, and inflicts bog.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Abilities<\/div><div>\\u30fb(Water) HP &amp; Strength +30%<\/div><div>If the user is attuned to Water, increases HP and strength by 30%.<\/div><div>\\u30fbDragon Time +20%<\/div><div>Extends shapeshift time by 20%.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The stats shown here represent the dragon at maximum level, maximum bond, and fully unbound. They do not represent the stats when first obtained.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The Fafnir Statue (Water) facility is described below.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Stats<\/div><div>\\u30fbHP +11.5%<\/div><div>\\u30fbStrength +11.5%<\/div><div>Boosts the HP and strength of water dragons.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The stats shown here represent the facility at maximum level. They do not represent the stats when first obtained.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>2. The Queen of the Blue Seas wyrmprint was added to the Imperial Onslaught section of the Treasure Trade menu.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The Queen of the Blue Seas wyrmprint is described below.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0 Abilities<\/div><div>\\u30fbHigh Mercury Res +25% (Max 25%)<\/div><div>\\u30fbMercury Res +20% (Max 25%)<\/div><div>\\u30fbWater Res +5% (Max 15%)<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>The stats shown here represent the wyrmprint at maximum level and fully unbound. They do not represent the stats when first obtained.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Notes:<\/div><div>1. In order to challenge High Mercury&#39;s Trial, a player&#39;s team must have 13,000 might or higher.<\/div><div>2. Players must have completed Mercury&#39;s Trial: Master to challenge High Mercury&#39;s Trial.<\/div><div>3. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 \/ 2-1 (Normal) of the campaign in order to play co-op.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div>","start_time":1555567200,"prev_article_id":"397","next_article_id":"388","image_path":"","update_time":1555468320}}}'